Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers
ANKARA , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Turkish newspapers Monday .
Sabah ( Morning )
-- Rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers ' Party ( PKK ) on Friday shot down a Turkish Sikorsky helicopter over Hakkari province at the Turkish-Iraqi border , killing 16 Turkish soldiers , wounding one .
The helicopter crashed when the pilot was shot by the PKK militants and lost control of the helicopter .
Hurriyet ( Freedom )
-- Turkish Democratic Left Party leader and Deputy Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit said that he will provide unconditional support for a new government to be formed by the central-right Motherland Party ( ANAP ) led by outgoing Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz and the central-right True Path Party ( DYP ) led by former Prime Minister Tansu Ciller .
The ANAP and the DYP formed a coalition in 1996 , but collapsed within three months .
Cumhuriyet ( Republic )
-- A statement issued by the Italian Embassy in Moscow said that if PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan can not be granted political asylum , he would be sent back to Russia .
Ocalan was detained by Italian police upon his arrival in Rome by a Russian Airlines passenger plane from Moscow on November 12 .
However , Italy rejected a Turkish warrant for the extradition of Ocalan under the Italian law barring extradition to countries where suspects may face death penalty .
